<area shape="rect" id="node1" title="dsgrid.config.dimension_mapping_base.DimensionMappingReferenceModel

Reference to a dimension mapping stored in the registry.

The DimensionMappingReferenceModel is utilized by the project configuration (project.json5) as well as by the
dimension mapping reference configuration (dimension_mapping_references.json5) that may be required when submitting a dataset to a project.

Attributes:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;from_dimension_type (DimensionType(DSGEnum)): Dimension Type
 &#160;&#160;&#160;to_dimension_type (DimensionType(DSGEnum)): Dimension Type
 &#160;&#160;&#160;mapping_id (str): Unique ID of the dimension mapping
 &#160;&#160;&#160;version (str): Version of the dimension
 &#160;&#160;&#160;required_for_validation (Optional[bool]): Set to False if a given dimension association is NOT required for input dataset validation; default is True. Default is True.
" alt="" coords="790,199,1289,367"/>
<area shape="rect" id="node2" title="dsgrid.config.project_config.InputDatasetModel

Defines an input dataset for the project config.

Attributes:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dataset_id (str): Unique dataset identifier.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dataset_type (InputDatasetType(DSGEnum)): Dataset type.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;version (str): Version of the registered dataset. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;required_dimensions (RequiredDimensionsModel): Defines required record IDs that must exist for each dimension. Default is single_dimensional=RequiredDimensionRecordsModel(geography=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]), metric=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]), model_year=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]), scenario=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]), sector=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]), subsector=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]), weather_year=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[])) multi_dimensional=[].
 &#160;&#160;&#160;mapping_references (List[DimensionMappingReferenceModel]): Defines how to map the dataset dimensions to the project. Default is [].
 &#160;&#160;&#160;status (DatasetRegistryStatus(DSGEnum)): Registration status of the dataset, added by dsgrid. Default is DatasetRegistryStatus.UNREGISTERED.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;wrap_time_allowed (bool): Whether to allow dataset time to be wrapped to project time if different. Default is False.
" alt="" coords="5,5,612,229"/>
<area shape="rect" id="node3" title="dsgrid.config.project_config.RequiredDimensionsModel

Defines required record IDs that must exist for each dimension in a dataset.
Record IDs can reside in the project&#39;s base, subset, or supplemental dimensions. Using subset
dimensions is recommended. dsgrid will substitute base records for mapped subset records
at runtime. If no records are listed for a dimension then all project base records are
required.

Attributes:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;single_dimensional (RequiredDimensionRecordsModel): Required records for a single dimension. Default is geography=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]) metric=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]) model_year=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]) scenario=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]) sector=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]) subsector=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]) weather_year=RequiredDimensionRecordsByTypeModel(base=[], subset=[], supplemental=[]).
 &#160;&#160;&#160;multi_dimensional (list[RequiredDimensionRecordsModel]): Required records for a combination of dimensions. For example, there may be a dataset requirement for only one subsector for a given sector instead of a cross product. Default is [].
" alt="" coords="756,66,1323,150"/>
